oul, the world, and God; rather it is through the force of imagination that these ideas are brought forth and made effective. A new preface situates the book in relation to Sallis's later work, and an extensive afterword focuses on Kant and the Greeks.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDialectic. 0aImagination. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aReason. 0aTranscendentalism. 4aPhilosophy : Epistemology. 4aPhilosophy : German Idealism. 4aPhilosophy : Hermeneutics. 4aPhilosophy : History of Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791483275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791483275/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles